                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Jackson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-07-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 13, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(In reply to dispatches Nos. 402 and 409, Mr. Bacon informs Mr. Jackson that the
                    Greeks therein referred to were specifically deported under alien contract law.
                    He adds that there is no objection to Greeks not of classes excluded by law
                    emigrating anywhere in the United States.)</p>
            </div>
